    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing configuration application in O1 set_config command\n\n### Summary\nThe O1 interface's `set_config` command in the telnet server was not applying parsed configuration parameters to the actual gNB configuration. While the function correctly parsed parameters like SSB frequency, ARFCN, bandwidth, and BWP settings, it never updated the underlying MAC configuration structures, making the command effectively a no-op.\n\nThis issue manifests when attempting to reconfigure the gNB through the O1 interface - the configuration values appear to be accepted but are never actually applied to the running system. Users would observe that subsequent `get_stats` calls still return the original configuration values.\n\nThe root cause was that the `set_config` function only parsed the input parameters but lacked the application logic present in similar functions like `set_bwconfig`. This fix adds the missing configuration application code that updates the ServingCellConfigCommon structure and reinitializes the MIB/SIB1 configurations.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_o1.c`: Added configuration application logic to `set_config` function to actually update the gNB configuration with parsed parameters\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_o1.c`: Enhanced parameter handling to optionally parse UL parameters (ARFCNUL, BWUL) with proper TDD/FDD support\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_o1.c`: Added proper reinitialization of MIB and SIB1 configurations following the same pattern as `set_bwconfig`\n\n"
}